Here's a proper Lit component in TypeScript that counts how many times it has been clicked and displays that count:

```typescript
import { html, customElement } from 'lit-element/lit-element.js';
import { property, state } from 'lit-element/directives/modular.js';

@customElement('click-counter')
class ClickCounter extends HTMLElement {
  @state() count = 0;

  connectedCallback() {
    super.connectedCallback();
    this.addEventListener('click', () => {
      this.count++;
      this.requestUpdate();
    });
  }

  render() {
    return html`
      <button>Click Me!</button>
      <p>Clicked ${this.count} times.</p>
    `;
  }
}

// If you are not using a bundler, you can register the property and state decorators
// at the global scope.
