Yes, you need to add CORS headers to your server to allow cross-origin requests.

CORS (Cross-Origin Resource Sharing) is a security feature implemented in web browsers to prevent web pages from making requests to a different origin (domain, protocol, or port) than the one the web page was loaded from.

To fix this issue, you need to add middleware to your Express server that sets the CORS headers. You can use the `cors` package for this.

**Install the cors package:**

```bash
npm install cors
```

**Update your server code:**

```javascript
const express = require('express');
const cors = require('cors');

const app = express();

// Middleware to parse JSON payloads
app.use(express.json());

// Middleware to enable CORS
const allowOrigin = 'http://localhost:3000';
const options = {
  origin: allowOrigin,
  methods: ['GET', 'POST'],
};
app.use(cors(options));

// GET request to http://localhost:8080/template
app.get('/template', (req, res) => {
  res.json({
    id: 1,
    sentence: "This is an $relevance sentence with $quantity alternatives",
    choices: {
      relevance: ['important', 'irrelevant'],
      quantity: ['few','some','many']
    }
  });
});

// POST request to http://localhost:8080/response
app.post('/response', (req, res) => {
  console.log(req.body);
  res.status(200).json({ message: 'Response received successfully' });
});

// Start server on port 8080
const PORT = 8080;
app.listen(PORT, () => {
  console.log(`Server listening on port ${PORT}`);
});
```

This code will set the allowed origin to `http://localhost:3000`, which should allow your client to make requests to your server.

**Production Use:**

In a production setting, you might want to set the origin dynamically or allow all origins. To do this, you can set the `origin` property to `*` which is a wildcard character that matches all origins.

```javascript
app.use(cors({
  origin: '*',
  methods: ['GET', 'POST'],
}));
```

This will allow any origin to make requests to your server; however, make sure to only include this in production code and avoid it in development code for security reasons.

