COBS FIFO Module
================

Overview
--------

The COBS (Consolidated Overnight Batch Secure) FIFO (First-In-First-Out) module is a C library designed to provide efficient and lossless data transmission over unreliable channels. The module uses the COBS encoding algorithm to serialize data into a format suitable for transmission, and a FIFO buffer to manage incoming and outgoing data.

Features
--------

*   Efficient use of bandwidth by compressing data using COBS encoding
*   Lossless data transmission due to the use of COBS encoding
*   Robust FIFO buffer management to prevent buffer overflows and underflows
*   Example usage code to simplify integration into existing projects

Installation
------------

To install the COBS FIFO module, simply copy the `cobs_fifo.h` and `cobs_fifo.c` files into your project directory. You will then need to compile the module along with any code that uses it.

Example Usage
-------------

Below is an example of how to use the COBS FIFO module in a simple data transmission application:

```c
#include <stdio.h>
#include <string.h>
#include "cobs_fifo.h"

int main() {
    // Initialize the FIFO buffer
    struct cobs_fifo_t *fifo = cobs_fifo_init(1024);

    // Add data to the FIFO buffer
    char data[] = "Hello, world!";
    cobs_fifo_enqueue(fifo, data, strlen(data));

    // Queue data to the FIFO
